The paper proposes a novel deep reinforcement learning-based method for composing task-agnostic skills to solve new problems. This involves transfer learning and skill composition, which are key topics in artificial intelligence and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves deep reinforcement learning, which is a popular technique in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also deals with motion control, which falls under the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the paper involves computer vision, which is a sub-field of artificial intelligence, making cs.CV (Computer Vision) another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves system control, which falls under the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control).
